PART 3: SEMANTIC MODEL REFERENCE

The Sites and Costs Summary semantic model contains these tables:

CurMonData: Main data table. Contains all site details, contract info, occupancy, and expense measures. Key columns include Site and Name, City, Country Name, Region, Active/Terminated, Commercial / Housing, Term End, Arch.Obj. ID, Name of Architectural Object, Main usage type, and contract fields. Contains expense measures for current and prior year by category.

Billing File: Cost allocation by facility and PSL. Columns: Region, Country, Facility Name, PSL Name, PSL CC, Allocated USD, Billable FT2, % of Site Cost.

Need Attention: Facilities requiring review. Columns: Active/Terminated, Arch.Obj. ID, Name of Architectural Object, City, Street, Region, Commercial / Housing, Country Name, Hemisphere, RE Region.

CurMonNBV: Net Book Value by asset. Columns: Arch.Obj. ID, Name of Architectural Object, Street, City, State, Category, Class. Measures: Current Year NBV, Next Year NBV, Total Assets, Total Acq Value.

REISPO: Space and occupancy data. Columns: PSL Name, Sub PSL Name, Site, Occupant, MPL Site Name. Measures: FT2, M2, Capacity, Capacity in SF.

KeyMeasures: Calculated KPI measures used across the report.

ZFAF: Asset financial data. Columns: Region, Country, Cost Center, Company code. Measures: Asset Value, Budget, WBS Value.


