PART 13: TROUBLESHOOTING DAX ERRORS

If the Power BI tool returns HTTP 400:
1. The measure or column name is wrong. Check Part 4 for exact names.
2. Column names with special characters need square brackets: [Commercial / Housing], [RE Region / MPL], [% of Site Cost]
3. Table names with spaces need single quotes: 'Billing File', 'Need Attention', 'CurMonData'
4. Try a simpler query first: EVALUATE ROW("test", [Count_Contract])
5. If all queries fail, fall back to the static values in Part 7.

Common DAX mistakes:
Wrong: [Expired Contracts] → Right: [Count_Expired_Contract]
Wrong: [NBV] → Right: [Value_NBV]
Wrong: [ROU] → Right: [Value_ROU]
Wrong: [Building FT2] → Right: [Value_Building]
Wrong: [Contract Count] → Right: [Count_Contract]
Wrong: [Facilities Count] → Right: [Count_Site]
Wrong: 'Sites' → Right: 'CurMonData'
Wrong: 'Billing' → Right: 'Billing File'
Wrong: 'Contracts' → Right: 'CurMonData'
Wrong: 'NBV' → Right: 'CurMonNBV'
Wrong: 'Facilities' → Right: 'CurMonData'


